     Search                           Programs & Applying     View Menu  Down arrow icon             In making one of your life's biggest decisions, start here.  If you're not a nurse but want to be, or if you're an RN wishing to advance your career to the next level, the UIC College of Nursing offers a program for you. At every level, our high-quality curricula are contemporary and evidence-based, incorporating cutting-edge research (much generated by our own distinguished and award-winning faculty). Students studying at any of our six campues—in Chicago, Peoria, Rockford, Quad Cities, Springfield or Urbana—experience a dynamic, student-centered school recognized as a leader in nursing education, research and practice.      Tiles        Tuition and financial aid information          Summary of application deadlines for all programs          Learn about our six campuses          Different Programs           Bachelor of Science in Nursing  The Nurse Generalist             Master of Science for non-RNs  The Career Changer             Master of Science for RNs  The Clinical Leader             Doctor of Nursing Practice  The Expert Clinician             Doctor of Philosophy  The Nurse Researcher             Certificate Programs  The Lifelong Learner              Programs & Applying    Back to main content           Find Your Program     Bachelor of Science in Nursing     Traditional BSN     Meet BSN students    Admissions & Applying     Admission Requirements    Apply Now      Sample Schedule    Clinical Experiences    BSN Info Sessions      RN to BSN      Master of Science for non-RNs     Meet AGMS/Grad-Entry Students    Clinical Experiences    Admission Requirements    Apply Now    MS Info Sessions      Master of Science for RNs     Meet MS Students    AGMS Transition Program    Admission Requirements    Apply Now    MS Info Sessions      Doctor of Nursing Practice     Meet DNP Students    DNP Focus Areas     Adult-Gerontology Acute Care Nurse Practitioner    Adult-Ge